5 Tricks For Weight Loss This Summer

Looking for weight gain recipes to bring in extra charm to your everyday life? Look nowhere beyond these amazing and easy-peasy milk-based recipes for a healthy weight gain! 1. Choco Almond smoothie Star ingredient in one recipe- chocolate, almonds and milk! Smoothie tastes a hell lot better when it has chocolate in it to tempt anyone. Add in your touch of health by including oats and banana in it. It is a filling recipe that is bound to gather some healthy weight. 2. Paneer Kofta Kofta made out of paneer or cottage cheese is a yummy accompaniment to any meals. Soft and spongy paneer in rich gravy not only tastes divine but is also good for weight gain. Have it with freshly cooked streamed rice or with chapattis and add some variety to your meals. 3. Mango Pudding Puddings are much loved in almost all seasons, be it summer or winters. Mango pudding when chilled is a delicious snack in itself. Use whole milk for some extra good fats but be sure to take control of portion size as excess might lead to digestive issues. 4. Rice kheer Any Indian festival is incomplete without kheer. Kheer can be made out of many ingredients but one constant ingredient is milk. When paired with rice, nuts, cardamom, the dessert is hard to resist. It is also a healthy and filling option. Over to you Weight gain might get challenging at times but with these simple recipes you are sure to put on some healthy weight but be sure to control added sugar and the portion size.
